-- ICAP Spot Currency Trading Volume on EBS Rose 17% in September
-- B y   L u c y   M e a k i n
-- 2012-10-04T14:39:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-04/icap-spot-currency-trading-volume-on-ebs-rose-17-in-september.html
ICAP Plc, the London-based
independent broking service, said currency trading volume on its
EBS electronic trading platform rose 17 percent in September
from a month earlier.  The average daily foreign-exchange volume was $111.9
billion last month, ICAP said in an e-mailed statement, down 39
percent from September 2011.  The volume of fixed-income products on the BrokerTec
platform increased 10 percent from August to $604.8 billion a
day, ICAP said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lucy Meakin in London at 
